Produced by: Yomiuri Telecasting Corp.
Tokyo Movie Co..Ltd.

10
00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:34.700
Please proceed to your cars.

11
00:01:35.190 --> 00:01:39.040
All racers.please proceed to your cars.

12
00:01:39.420 --> 00:01:42.910
In pole position number 17 
Jackie Stewart in the Ford Tyrrell.

13
00:01:43.190 --> 00:01:46.750
Number 18 is Denis Hulme in a McLaren.
Say.What Are You Doing With That Can?

14
00:01:46.780 --> 00:01:49.660
Num 4 Lupan The 3RD...
I was just checking the oil...

15
00:01:50.650 --> 00:01:51.740
Oil?Huh?

16
00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:53.620
Are you in charge of 
maintaining this car?

17
00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:55.510
Not exactly...

18
00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:56.960
Well.then.we don't need your help.

19
00:01:57.230 --> 00:01:59.360
This car's already been well cared for.

20
00:01:59.470 --> 00:02:00.350
Ye-Yessir!!

21
00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:04.900
Jigen. this is Lupan.

22
00:02:05.150 --> 00:02:07.300
As expected.some shady guys
 are nosing around here.

23
00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:09.440
How are things where you are?

24
00:02:10.370 --> 00:02:12.330
Very peaceful.

25
00:02:12.510 --> 00:02:14.360
The birds are chirping a tune.

26
00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:16.000
I am not asking about you.

27
00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:19.720
How's my lover. Fujiko Mine?
Have you heard from here?

28
00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:21.770
Your "lover"?

29
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:24.970
Seems like she Infiltrated 
Hotel Miracle just fine.

30
00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:27.730
I haven't heard form her since.

31
00:02:27.760 --> 00:02:29.510
I'm sure she'll be fine. though.

32
00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:36.140
Now.ladies and gentlemen.
the purpose today's meeting...

33
00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:41.470
...is to conduct the funeral of scorpion's
old enemy.Lupan The 3RD!

34
00:02:41.830 --> 00:02:46.010
It's true Lupan yet lives.
but he will soon die.

35
00:02:46.200 --> 00:02:50.500
And we will enjoy witnessing
 his death together.

36
00:02:52.600 --> 00:02:56.320
However...First things first.

37
00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:00.440
Dammit!

38
00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:07.130
This is Jigen Daisuke.
 What's the latest?

39
00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:11.260
Oh. Jigen. Please hurry and tell
Lupan that Scorpio's planning to...

40
00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:21.590
Is Lupan Burning?!
(Rupan wa Moeteiruka....?!)

41
00:03:36.650 --> 00:03:42.330
I knew what you were up to.
but I've left you alone till now.

42
00:03:42.690 --> 00:03:46.450
If we made a fuss and Lupan got
 wise to it.our plans for this...

43
00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:51.280
...funeral might be have ruined...
Makes sense. doesn't it?

44
00:03:52.850 --> 00:03:56.950
Isn't this all just indulgent child's play.
even by Scorpion standards?

45
00:03:57.030 --> 00:04:02.480
Yes. and you are going to add
spice to this "child's play."

46
00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:06.170
You want me to be a baton
girl for Lupan's funeral?

47
00:04:06.670 --> 00:04:08.370
Well. that won't happen.

48
00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:10.390
Lupan is indestructible!

49
00:04:10.410 --> 00:04:17.080
Before now.perhaps. But this time 
Ms. Mine.I would gladly wager on his death!

50
00:04:24.820 --> 00:04:26.420
Hida Speedway...

51
00:04:26.840 --> 00:04:31.220
...built in 5 years and at a 
cost of 5 billion yen.

52
00:04:31.510 --> 00:04:33.940
We made it the largest of it's 
kind in the Eastern world.

53
00:04:34.090 --> 00:04:38.340
Today is host to it's inaugural 
Grand-Prix race...

54
00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:41.090
...we assumed the identity of
 the Japan Racing Alliance

55
00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:43.850
to issue an invitation to 
one special racer.

56
00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:46.910
The driver of that Ferrari 312B.

57
00:04:47.520 --> 00:04:50.780
This man. That's right. Lupan The 3RD!

58
00:04:50.930 --> 00:04:53.800
He's usually very careful.

59
00:04:53.850 --> 00:04:57.340
But when it comes to racing.he's
hooked with a simple invitation.

60
00:04:57.360 --> 00:05:00.390
Humans are interesting like that. don't you think. Ms. Mine?

61
00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:02.120
How does this make any sense?

62
00:05:02.310 --> 00:05:06.600
You've spent 5 billion yen to build 
a racetrack just to kill one man?

63
00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:10.970
I am not just getting rid of Lupan....

64
00:05:11.280 --> 00:05:15.160
...I'm crushing the very symbol
 of the Lupan Empire.

65
00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:20.830
My rivals. without his support.
will crumble in no time.

66
00:05:22.750 --> 00:05:24.980
The race is about to start.

67
00:05:25.500 --> 00:05:28.870
It's a turbulent course with mountains.valleys....

68
00:05:28.940 --> 00:05:32.160
...and maybe even a surprise
 pothole. you see?

69
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:37.680
Thanks to the hundred cameras we've set up
around the racetrack. we'll see the entire thing.

70
00:05:37.810 --> 00:05:43.900
And. Ms. Mine. as you watch the events
unfold. you will slowly die.yourself.

71
00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:19.140
Jigen.sorry for the wait.

72
00:06:19.340 --> 00:06:22.070
I feel great and so does this machine!

73
00:06:22.130 --> 00:06:24.380
Lupan.something's wrong here.

74
00:06:24.600 --> 00:06:27.350
It's been over thirty minutes
since we've lost contact with her.

75
00:06:28.550 --> 00:06:31.140
Hmm. So she fell into enemy hands.

76
00:06:31.650 --> 00:06:32.790
Well. that's Okay.

77
00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:36.010
Hey. how can you say such a thing?

78
00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:40.280
According to the CIA's statistics research. the
percentage of spies' covers being blown...

79
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:42.020
Heh. Anyhow.

80
00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:45.300
Fujiko has been caught
And I'm deep into their trap.

81
00:06:45.710 --> 00:06:49.470
They'll get comfortable and when
their guard is down. I'll strike.

82
00:06:49.810 --> 00:06:51.650
"Trap?" Did you say"trap"?

83
00:06:52.330 --> 00:06:53.550
Then. this race is...

84
00:06:53.690 --> 00:06:54.470
That's right.

85
00:06:54.700 --> 00:06:57.540
All these cars.these
 racers..they're supposedly top class.

86
00:06:58.180 --> 00:07:00.280
John Surtees in a Surtees TS7.

87
00:07:00.690 --> 00:07:02.500
Jackie Stewart in a Ford Tyrrell.

88
00:07:03.160 --> 00:07:04.780
Denny Hulme in a McLaren.

89
00:07:05.990 --> 00:07:07.890
Beltoise in a Matra-Simca.

90
00:07:08.830 --> 00:07:11.670
But you can tell by their technique 
that they're impostors.

91
00:07:12.610 --> 00:07:15.080
The cars are disguised well. but
 their sounds give them away.

92
00:07:15.490 --> 00:07:17.460
They've all been manufactured by
 Scorpion subsidiaries.

93
00:07:18.890 --> 00:07:22.130
I don't know what kind
of trap they have prepared for me.

94
00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:25.870
I knew exactly what this was 
as from the get-go.

95
00:07:26.640 --> 00:07:28.160
Lupan. enough chatter.

96
00:07:28.550 --> 00:07:29.770
You've got another car on your tail!

97
00:07:30.020 --> 00:07:31.040
A Lotus 72.

98
00:07:49.180 --> 00:07:50.940
Lupan. is it "Scorpion"?

99
00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:54.200
No..not him.it's our rival. from the
Tokyo Metropolitan Police

100
00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:55.390
Inspector Zenigata

101
00:07:59.060 --> 00:08:00.180
Zenigata...

102
00:08:22.990 --> 00:08:27.160
Lupan. How many years
has it been chasing you like this.

103
00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:29.640
It's in my blood.

104
00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:31.580
It's fate.

105
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:34.480
If you weren't the grandson
 of Arsêne Lupan .

106
00:08:35.420 --> 00:08:37.900
And If I weren't a descendant
of Heiji Zenigata.

107
00:08:42.420 --> 00:08:44.680
I'm going to arrest you
 for sure some day.

108
00:08:46.820 --> 00:08:50.450
You are a pretentious scoundrel...
I am sure to catch you today!

109
00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:52.830
I'll arrest you today.

110
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:56.230
There's no doubt you'll do
 something here today.

111
00:08:56.640 --> 00:08:59.790
I'll never take my eye
off your car no matter what happens.

112
00:09:05.600 --> 00:09:07.930
This is the commissioner to all mechanics.

113
00:09:08.020 --> 00:09:12.390
Initiate the "Lupan The 3RD
 Execution Plan"as instructed

114
00:09:12.940 --> 00:09:13.710
Roger!

115
00:09:15.300 --> 00:09:17.290
The show has started.

116
00:09:17.490 --> 00:09:20.650
So. let's start. too. Ms. Mine.

117
00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:51.310
It has to look like an accident...
But Lupan's a sharp one.

118
00:09:51.510 --> 00:09:55.400
Even at 200 kilometers an hour. he
spotted the anomaly on the road.

119
00:09:56.090 --> 00:09:59.760
He certainly deserves his class-"A" license

120
00:10:14.050 --> 00:10:15.410
Darn!

121
00:10:23.190 --> 00:10:25.490
Jigen. the fun's starting.

122
00:10:26.090 --> 00:10:27.760
Let's show them some fun of our own.

123
00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:28.890
All right!

124
00:12:02.590 --> 00:12:03.750
The Water Department?

125
00:12:04.220 --> 00:12:05.420
A plumbing problem?

126
00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:10.990
Yes.We received a phone call from
 your hotel that the flushing system...

127
00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:13.150
...of the employee-only
 toilets are out of order.

128
00:12:13.170 --> 00:12:15.200
Strange.I have no record 
of such a call...

129
00:12:15.280 --> 00:12:17.460
Well. if it's been a mistake.
 that's fine. too.

130
00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:18.840
Hey. you!you!

131
00:12:19.060 --> 00:12:20.690
Please wait and take a look anyway!

132
00:12:21.050 --> 00:12:21.960
Sure.

133
00:12:26.480 --> 00:12:28.420
Here is the place. Please make it quick.

134
00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:29.710
Yes.

135
00:12:29.880 --> 00:12:33.910
Let's see...I think they said
it was the lady's toilet.

136
00:12:46.080 --> 00:12:50.870
Oh.this is no good. something's
stuck. No. It won't do.

137
00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:24.730
You...You are Lupan!

138
00:13:24.840 --> 00:13:25.830
Goodnight!

139
00:14:06.380 --> 00:14:10.920
Ah! Stop...no!I can't breathe...
Please...no!

140
00:14:10.970 --> 00:14:12.070
can't breathe!

141
00:14:12.680 --> 00:14:14.840
I can't breathe!

142
00:14:18.740 --> 00:14:19.590
Stop it!

143
00:14:30.920 --> 00:14:35.980
How do you feel now? Lupan is one 
step from death...How about you?

144
00:14:40.750 --> 00:14:42.580
Please open up!open the door!

145
00:14:42.880 --> 00:14:43.750
Wha...

146
00:14:43.850 --> 00:14:46.140
what's going on?!
Guards. go check it out!

147
00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:56.130
Wa... Water!?

148
00:14:57.090 --> 00:15:00.440
What's with this water!Hurry!
Shut the door quick!Hurry up!

149
00:15:01.350 --> 00:15:04.450
Commissioner!It's Lupan... Lupan did it!

150
00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:06.010
Wha...what!? Don't be a moron!

151
00:15:07.290 --> 00:15:08.430
Look over there!.

152
00:15:08.740 --> 00:15:10.810
Unless there's been some
 kind of miracle.Lupan...

153
00:15:10.820 --> 00:15:13.000
A miracle it was. then.

154
00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:14.630
Eh?

155
00:15:18.370 --> 00:15:20.270
- Lupan?
- Lupan!

156
00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:21.180
Lupan!

157
00:15:21.260 --> 00:15:25.140
That's right. It's not unnatural for a miracle
 to occur in a hotel named "miracle".

158
00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:27.770
Now. how about we start
 the funeral for Scorpion?

159
00:15:30.400 --> 00:15:32.350
Shoot him! Shoot him!

160
00:15:51.100 --> 00:15:53.140
Hey. Fujiko. How are you?

161
00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:56.240
Oh. I'm so-so. Mr. Lupan.

162
00:15:57.120 --> 00:16:00.710
But. since you were coming. I wish
you could have come a bit sooner

163
00:16:01.450 --> 00:16:05.710
No. no.on the contrary. I think I
should have come a little bit later.

164
00:16:46.020 --> 00:16:48.780
Zenigata. old man. you're
not a bad driver...

165
00:16:48.850 --> 00:16:52.080
...but my car is a lot better.
So. don't take this too hard.

166
00:17:24.110 --> 00:17:25.200
Hey. Lil' Red Riding Hood.

167
00:17:25.200 --> 00:17:27.630
So. how was
Scorpion castle?

168
00:17:27.780 --> 00:17:29.550
Umm... It was nothing special.

169
00:17:30.520 --> 00:17:32.930
What about you?
How did you like being a racer?

170
00:17:36.860 --> 00:17:39.230
Now then...
It's time to put an end to this.

171
00:18:17.600 --> 00:18:22.040
The three winning drivers
will approach the stand...

172
00:18:37.250 --> 00:18:39.150
Damn... I was hoping he'd pull
something during the race...

173
00:18:39.220 --> 00:18:41.240
...but the only thing
he stole today was speed.

174
00:18:41.680 --> 00:18:42.280
Huh?

175
00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:45.690
13

176
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:46.570
12

177
00:18:47.130 --> 00:18:47.780
11

178
00:18:48.400 --> 00:18:48.930
10

179
00:18:49.450 --> 00:18:50.070
9

180
00:18:50.500 --> 00:18:51.240
8

181
00:18:51.550 --> 00:18:52.150
7

182
00:18:52.650 --> 00:18:53.280
6

183
00:18:53.750 --> 00:18:54.340
5

184
00:18:54.730 --> 00:18:55.360
4

185
00:18:55.500 --> 00:18:56.720
Hey. chairman!

186
00:18:56.820 --> 00:18:57.370
Yes?

187
00:18:57.750 --> 00:18:58.850
Present!

188
00:19:14.070 --> 00:19:17.450
-After him! After him!
-Hold it!

189
00:19:19.820 --> 00:19:21.400
I knew it!

190
00:19:24.150 --> 00:19:25.910
Idiot! What. do you think
 I'll let you stop me?!

191
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:28.400
Not at all. But stay here if 
you don't want to die.

192
00:19:28.450 --> 00:19:29.300
What?

193
00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:33.370
It's time.

194
00:19:33.670 --> 00:19:36.880
3... 2... 1... 0.

195
00:19:54.600 --> 00:19:57.420
Well.well. If it isn't the honorable
 Zenigata. It's been a while.

196
00:19:57.830 --> 00:19:59.000
Lupan! What the...

197
00:20:17.340 --> 00:20:19.230
It's burning! It's burning!

198
00:20:19.270 --> 00:20:21.160
Lupan is burning!

199
00:20:37.550 --> 00:20:39.710
Scoundrel! What have you done?

200
00:20:39.820 --> 00:20:42.250
Hey! I have got an alibi.

201
00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:44.380
And you are my witness.

202
00:20:44.450 --> 00:20:46.030
Of all people. Well done. Inspector.

203
00:20:48.570 --> 00:20:51.750
After all.you were right behind my
car during the whole race.

204
00:20:52.470 --> 00:20:54.150
Don't take me for a fool. Lupan!

205
00:20:55.350 --> 00:20:58.770
You think that I'm just
a third-class police officer.

206
00:20:58.850 --> 00:20:59.850
But you're wrong!

207
00:21:00.600 --> 00:21:04.280
I know what you've
done. I have a witness.

208
00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:06.860
The trick has been exposed.

209
00:21:08.360 --> 00:21:09.130
see?

210
00:21:09.170 --> 00:21:13.250
Ah! Jigen! No. No...
Who is this guy?

211
00:21:17.690 --> 00:21:18.330
Huh?

212
00:21:19.670 --> 00:21:21.780
Fujiko! So. you were...

213
00:21:22.210 --> 00:21:25.460
That's right. Fujiko Mine was
working with me from the start.

214
00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:27.500
Lupan. you are under arrest!

215
00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:32.130
So. Mr. Zenigata. This seals the deal.

216
00:21:32.580 --> 00:21:34.080
Now please.give me
 what you promised.

217
00:21:34.510 --> 00:21:35.990
Yes.I'm a man of my word.

218
00:21:36.980 --> 00:21:37.800
Here it is!

219
00:21:39.810 --> 00:21:41.650
An arrest warrant!?
Is it yours?

220
00:21:41.970 --> 00:21:44.490
That's right. And now. I'm free.

221
00:21:45.440 --> 00:21:46.930
Lupan. I'm sorry.

222
00:21:56.230 --> 00:22:00.030
Indeed. freedom is mankind's
 most valuable asset.

223
00:22:00.220 --> 00:22:04.450
But for you Lupan. a life without
freedom awaits. Come along.

224
00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:10.310
There's no use fighting
 it. so get moving now.

225
00:22:11.930 --> 00:22:15.800
You're wasting your time in resisting!
You can't escape from me!

226
00:22:40.510 --> 00:22:42.480
So. Are you here to kill a traitor?

227
00:22:42.730 --> 00:22:46.900
Oh no!nothing like that. for women.
betrayal is just another accessory.

228
00:22:47.040 --> 00:22:50.850
No one could love a woman if they let
 that get to them. Isn't that right?

229
00:22:51.980 --> 00:22:54.160
Stop it! Sto...

230
00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:11.720
Hey. what's up? In next week's
 episode. a strange man appears.

231
00:23:11.770 --> 00:23:14.300
His name is Pycal. He 
sounds like a drunkard.

232
00:23:14.830 --> 00:23:18.840
He can deflect Bullets like they're nothing 
and shoot crimson fire from his fingertips.

233
00:23:18.950 --> 00:23:21.000
He's even giving me a rough time!

234
00:23:21.460 --> 00:23:23.850
Up next week:
"the man they called a magician"

235
00:23:23.850 --> 00:23:25.720
You'll just have to wait
 to see me in action.

236
00:23:25.740 --> 00:23:27.050
I'll see ya on this channel!

237
00:23:33.100 --> 00:23:42.100
He kicks off the red waves

238
00:23:42.730 --> 00:23:51.430
That entwine around his feet

239
00:23:52.250 --> 00:23:56.440
As machine guns scream.

240
00:23:57.010 --> 00:24:05.800
Resembling the crazy morning light. it's his

241
00:24:06.460 --> 00:24:10.750
Walther P-38.

242
00:24:11.360 --> 00:24:15.760
Everything he holds.

243
00:24:16.200 --> 00:24:19.670
In his own two hands.

244
00:24:20.220 --> 00:24:24.730
Is bound by fate

245
00:24:25.650 --> 00:24:29.280
To disappear on him

246
00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:34.650
Lupan the 3RD.

247
00:24:35.270 --> 00:24:39.180
Lupan the 3RD.

